24
00:01:16,642 --> 00:01:19,331
Cities in low- 
and middle-income countries

25
00:01:19,406 --> 00:01:21,742
are often highly heterogeneous.

26
00:01:22,209 --> 00:01:23,750
Roughly, we can distinguish

27
00:01:23,909 --> 00:01:26,177
between middle- 
and high-income settlements.

28
00:01:26,474 --> 00:01:30,323
informal settlements
and the peri-urban interface.

29
00:01:31,786 --> 00:01:33,681
We can add
to these three categories

30
00:01:33,743 --> 00:01:35,556
the newly-planned urban areas.

31
00:01:36,296 --> 00:01:39,547
Sometimes, the different contexts
are clearly separated

32
00:01:39,609 --> 00:01:40,846
in large neighborhoods.

33
00:01:41,219 --> 00:01:43,390
But sometimes,
they are also more scattered,

34
00:01:44,071 --> 00:01:45,034
like some pockets.

35
00:01:45,669 --> 00:01:49,169
Each context may require
different sanitation solutions.

36
00:01:49,928 --> 00:01:51,719
Often, when you arrive
in a city,

37
00:01:52,165 --> 00:01:54,539
the city center is served
by a sewer network.

38
00:01:55,104 --> 00:01:57,344
The main question is then
what to do

39
00:01:57,419 --> 00:01:59,803
with the area surrounding
the city center?

40
00:02:00,434 --> 00:02:02,805
